de.akquinet.android.androlog
Class Log

java.lang.Object
  de.akquinet.android.androlog.Log

public class Log
extends java.lang.Object

Implements a small layer on top of the Android Log to provide programmatic enabling and disabling of logging.

init

public static void init(java.lang.String fileName)
Android init method. This method uses the Android API. Inits the logger by reading the file: /SDCARD/fileName. The file must be a valid Java properties file.

Parameters:
fileName - the file name

init

public static void init(android.content.Context context)
Android init method. This method uses the Android API. This methods computes the package (Context.getPackageName()) of the application configuring the logger, and initializes the logger with a property file named 'package.properties' on the SDCARD. If the file is readable and exist, the Log is configured. The file must be a valid Java properties file.

See Also:
Properties

init

public static void init()
Android init method. This method uses the Android API. It reads the ANDROLOG_PROPERTIES file on the SDCARD. If the file is readable and exist, the Log is configured. The file must be a valid Java properties file.

isLoggable

public static boolean isLoggable(java.lang.String tag,
                                 int level)
Checks to see whether or not a log for the specified tag is loggable at the specified level. The default level of any tag is set as specified in setDefaultLogLevel(int). This means that any level above and including that level will be logged. Use configure(Properties) to define different log levels for each tag.

Parameters:
tag - The tag to check.
level - The level to check.
Returns:
Whether or not that this is allowed to be logged.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is thrown if the tag.length() > 23.
